<ul>
<li>Avg. Daily Rate: RM 220</li>
<li>Occupancy: 70%</li>
<li>Monthly Revenue: RM 11,550 (52 nights × RM 220)</li>
<li>Annual Gross: RM 138,600</li>
<li>Annual Expenses: RM 15,000</li>
<li><strong>Net Annual: RM 123,600</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Scenario B: Homestay Model</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Avg. Daily Rate: RM 120</li>
<li>Occupancy: 85%</li>
<li>Monthly Revenue: RM 5,610 (47 nights × RM 120)</li>
<li>Annual Gross: RM 67,320</li>
<li>Annual Expenses: RM 8,000</li>
<li><strong>Net Annual: RM 59,320</strong></li>
</ul>
<strong>Winner: Airbnb earns 108% more</strong>
<p><strong>However:</strong> Airbnb requires more work (cleaning, guest communication, maintenance)</p>
<hr class="my-8">
<h2>Operational Differences</h2>
<h3>Airbnb Operations</h3>
<p><strong>Daily Tasks:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Guest communication (messaging platform)</li>
<li>Booking management (calendar sync)</li>
<li>Cleaning coordination (between every stay)</li>
<li>Linen service (wash, replace)</li>
<li>Maintenance requests</li>
<li>Review management</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Time Commitment:</strong> 5-10 hours/week (if self-managed)</p>
<p><strong>Or:</strong> Hire management company (RM 200-400/month)</p>
<h3>Homestay Operations</h3>
<p><strong>Daily Tasks:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Guest interaction (breakfast, dinner)</li>
<li>Light housekeeping (guest cleans own room)</li>
<li>Laundry assistance</li>
<li>Local guidance (recommendations, directions)</li>
<li>Cultural exchange activities</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Time Commitment:</strong> 2-4 hours/day (host presence required)</p>
<p><strong>Family Impact:</strong> Requires lifestyle adjustment
<hr class="my-8">
<h2>Pros & Cons</h2>
<h3>Airbnb Pros</h3>
<ul>
<li>Higher income potential (2× homestay)</li>
<li>No host presence required</li>
<li>Flexible (block dates for personal use)</li>
<li>Professional operations (scalable)</li>
<li>Multiple property portfolio possible</li>
</ul>
<h3>Airbnb Cons</h3>
<ul>
<li>Higher operating costs (cleaning, platform fees)</li>
<li>More regulations (licensing, strata)</li>
<li>Guest turnover (cleaning after every stay)</li>
<li>Requires professional setup (furnishing, amenities)</li>
<li>Competitive market (pricing pressure)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Homestay Pros</h3>
<ul>
<li>Steady, long-term bookings</li>
<li>Lower operating costs</li>
<li>Cultural exchange experience</li>
<li>Simpler setup (basic furnishing)</li>
<li>Less competition</li>
</ul>
<h3>Homestay Cons</h3>
<ul>
<li>Lower income</li>
<li>Host presence required (lifestyle impact)</li>
<li>Limited scalability (can only manage 1-2 properties)</li>
<li>Personal space shared</li>
<li>Requires family participation</li>
</ul>
<hr class="my-8">
<h2>Which Model Should You Choose?</h2>
<h3>Choose Airbnb If:</h3>
<ul>
<li>You want maximum income</li>
<li>You don't live in the property</li>
<li>You want professional management</li>
<li>You want to build a property portfolio</li>
<li>You value flexibility (personal use)</li>
<li>You're targeting tourist/weekend market</li>
</ul>
<h3>Choose Homestay If:</h3>
<ul>
<li>You live in the property</li>
<li>You enjoy cultural exchange</li>
<li>You want steady, long-term guests</li>
<li>You're near universities/hospitals</li>
<li>You don't want high turnover</li>
<li>You prefer simpler operations</li>
</ul>
<h3>Hybrid Model (Best of Both)</h3>
<p>Some owners do both:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Airbnb:</strong> Weekends/holidays (higher rates)</li>
<li><strong>Homestay:</strong> Weekdays/monthly guests (steady base)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Requires careful scheduling</p>
